[ProMED-mail is indebted to Professor Henttonen for provision of some
of the detail missing from previous reports of HFRS from this region.
It is interesting to learn that greater access to forest regions as a
result of the dissolution of the Soviet Union may be playing a role
in increasing the prevalence of HFRS in the new Republics in addition
to the more predictable roles of rodent population fluctuations and
climate change.

The Republics of Tatarstan and Udmurtia can be located by accessing
the interactive map of Russia available at
<http://map.rin.ru/index_e.html>.
- Mod.CP]
